<TITLE> 20 dead in Daudkandi bus collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 7 (bdnews24.com)At least 20 people died in a road crash Monday morning involving two buses colliding head-on at Daudkandi on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway. Daudkandi police chief Abdur Rab told bdnews24.com that a Dhaka-bound Starline Transport Company coach travelling from Feni rammed into a Comilla-bound minibus coming from Homna, veering from the road to hit roadside trees before crashing into a ditch. The collision took place at around 8.45am, at Doulatpur near Eliotgunje, Daudkandi, Abdur Rab said. Identities of six of the deceased could be ascertained, the Starline bus driver Nayan (38), Salma (35), Nasir (42), Akbar Hossain (30), Alam (38) and Mannan (19), the police chief said. The bus was recovered with no bodies remaining inside, he said. Most of the injured 15 were admitted to Gouripur Hospital, others were sent to Dhaka. bdnews2
